      "h2": "Hearing loops",
      "h3s": [],
      "paragraphs": [
        "Sometimes referred to as an audio induction loop, hearing loops are an assistive technology that allows hearing device users to have sound broadcasted directly to their hearing devices when the device is set to the “T” (Telecoil) setting.",
        "Hearing loops are available at all JFK terminals at the following locations:"
      ],
